log_entry: Engine #2 EGT reading was 5 degrees above normal during cruise.
FMS failed to load SID from database, manual entry required.
Left main landing gear tire pressure sensor showing intermittent low values.
APU generator fault light illuminated for 7 seconds post-shutdown.
Cabin pressure controller B reported an error, switched to A.
TCAS advisory 'TRAFFIC' with no visual confirmation.
Wing anti-ice system valve on the right side was slow to open.
NAV display on captain's side was blank for 5s during flight.
Fuel pump in center tank shows fluctuating output pressure.
Error message 'CONFIG' on EICAS during takeoff roll.
Emergency locator transmitter self-test failed.
VHF Comm radio 2 produced static noise.
Galley oven circuit breaker tripped.
GPWS 'TERRAIN' warning, confirmed false alert due to database issue.
Flight director bars disappeared for a few seconds.
High vibration detected on engine #1 fan blade, requires inspection.
Slats extension was slower than the flaps.
Oxygen mask microphone in the cockpit is not working.
Received 'DOOR NOT CLOSED' indication for forward cargo.
Engine #1 suffered a bird strike on final approach. Visible damage.
